title: SHELL - Official Trailer (2025) Elisabeth Moss, Kate Hudson

author: IGN
description: High above the little town of Grubbers Nubbin, in a castle laboratory, the maddest of all mad professors brings monstrous creations to (almost) life… and then promptly forgets all about them. So, who runs the castle? Who keeps the monsters in line, so the townsfolk don’t form an angry mob? That job falls to Stitch Head - the professor’s very first creation. He does it all, unnoticed and unthanked. But when a ramshackle freak show rolls into town, its sly owner, Fulbert Freakfinder, comes knocking, offering Stitch Head fame, fortune… and maybe even love. A whimsical, heartfelt twist on the Frankenstein legend, STITCH HEAD is a comedy adventure for monsters of every age.
title: Stitch Head - Official Teaser Trailer (2025)

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the Official Trailer for Lost Contact: UFOs After Wartime, a documentary based on World War 2 sightings of unidentified flying objects distributed by Small Town Monsters. Explore the tragic story of World War 2 pilot Thomas Mantell Jr. in Lost Contact: UFOs After Wartime, releasing exclusively on October 7 on Amazon Prime Video and Vimeo on Demand.

Records suggest that UFO encounters were prevalent across multiple theaters during World War II, but that’s not when the sightings ended. On January 7, 1948, WWII veteran Captain Thomas Mantell, Jr. lost his life while serving for the Kentucky Air National Guard as he chased an unidentified flying object. Lost Contact: UFOs After Wartime examines not only the timeline of events surrounding Mantell’s death, but also the long-lasting impact on his loved ones.

Lost Contact: UFOs After Wartime releases exclusively on October 7 on Amazon Prime Video and Vimeo on Demand.
title: Lost Contact: UFOs After Wartime - Official Trailer (2025) Documentary

author: IGN
description: Here's your look at the Lootbane announcement trailer for this upcoming loot-driven RPG, where loot is power, risk is everything, and every decision can make or break your journey. In Lootbane, players choose their hero, venture across dangerous lands, and build a warband of vagabonds united by loot-powered synergy. Unique passive auras and active abilities stack in creative ways, while randomized gear ensures no two runs are alike.
title: Lootbane - Official Announce Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the 'I Think We Got That' Clip from Springsteen: Deliver Me From Nowhere, an upcoming film centered on the life and career of the legendary Bruce Springsteen, portrayed by Jeremy Allen White. Springsteen: Deliver Me From Nowhere is in theaters on October 24.

The film chronicles the making of Bruce Springsteen’s 1982 Nebraska album. Recorded on a four-track recorder in Springsteen’s New Jersey bedroom, the album marked a pivotal time in his life and is considered one of his most enduring works—a raw, haunted acoustic record populated by lost souls searching for a reason to believe. 

Starring Jeremy Allen White as Bruce Springsteen, the film is directed by Scott Cooper from his adaptation of Warren Zanes’ book of the same name. Springsteen: Deliver Me from Nowhere also features Jeremy Strong as Springsteen’s long-time confidant and manager, Jon Landau; Paul Walter Hauser; Odessa Young; Stephen Graham; Gaby Hoffman; David Krumholtz and Matthew Pellicano Jr.
